               <msContents>
                  <summary>Teaching from the Sages of France and Ashkenaz, and answers of the Geonim</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <title xml:lang="he">הוראות מחכמי צרפת ואשכנז ותשובות הגאונים</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hora'ot me-ḥakhame Tsarfat ṿe-Ashkenaz ṿe-teshovot ha-Ge'onim</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                     <note>According to <persName ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/79163724">Avraham Grossman</persName> (Jerusalem, 1981), 460, the decisions in this MS. were collected by a pupil of <persName key="person_49010383">Isaac b. Samuel of Dampierre</persName>.</note>
                     <note>Also quoted in the manuscript are <persName><lang xml:lang="he">הר"ר מאיר מריינשבורק</lang> Rabbi Meir of Reinsburg</persName> (<locus>fol. 20v</locus>) and <persName><lang xml:lang="he">הר"ר אליקים כהן מפריזבורק</lang> Rabbi Eliakim Cohen of Friesburg</persName> (<locus>fol. 34v</locus>).</note>
